    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @terranboy,\r\n\r\nThe routing example doesn't demonstrate what you are trying to achieve currently. It's up to you to decide how you want the `searchState` to be transformed as an url.\r\n\r\nWhat you could add is a clean up function that will remove any empty objects and any empty strings from the `searchState`.\r\n\r\nEx:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport {omitBy, toPairs, isEmpty, isObject} from 'lodash';\r\n\r\nconst searchState = toPairs(nextSearchState).reduce((acc, pair) => {\r\n      const value = isObject(pair[1]) ? omitBy(pair[1], v => v === '') : pair[1];\r\n      if (value !== '' && !isEmpty(value)) {\r\n        acc[pair[0]] = value;\r\n      }\r\n      return acc;\r\n    }, {});\r\n```\r\n\r\nLet me know if this help. ",
